<p id="p0135" class="p">We suppose that farmer 
 <italic class="italic">n</italic> faces 
 <italic class="italic">K</italic> alternatives contained in choice set 
 <italic class="italic">ψ</italic> during situation 
 <italic class="italic">s</italic>. We define an underlying latent variable 
 <italic class="italic">V</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">njs</italic>
 </sub>
 <sup class="sup">∗</sup> that denotes the value function associated with farmer 
 <italic class="italic">n</italic> choosing option 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic> ∈ 
 <italic class="italic">ψ</italic> during choice situation 
 <italic class="italic">s</italic>. Farmer 
 <italic class="italic">n</italic> will choose alternative 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic> so long as 
 <italic class="italic">V</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">njs</italic>
 </sub>
 <sup class="sup">∗</sup> &gt; 
 <italic class="italic">V</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">nks</italic>
 </sub>
 <sup class="sup">∗</sup> ∀ 
 <italic class="italic">k</italic> ≠ 
 <italic class="italic">j</italic>. Indirect utility 
 <italic class="italic">V</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">njs</italic>
 </sub>
 <sup class="sup">∗</sup> is not directly observed; what is observed is the actual utility maximizing choice 
 <italic class="italic">V</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">njs</italic>
 </sub>, where
 <disp-formula id="fo0005" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(1)</label>
  <math id="M1" display="block" altimg="si1.gif" overflow="scroll" class="math">
   <msub class="msub">
    <mi class="mi">V</mi>
    <mi mathvariant="italic" class="mi">njs</mi>
   </msub>
   <mo class="mo">=</mo>
   <mfenced open="{" class="mfenced">
    <mtable class="mtable">
     <mtr class="mtr">
      <mtd class="mtd">
       <maligngroup class="maligngroup"/>
